&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sunday everything is closed. Yes, really. Here&amp;rsquo;s how to adapt — and what you might actually prefer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;🇹🇷 Turkey: Open, Loud, and Always Available
 &lt;div id="-turkey-open-loud-and-always-available" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#-turkey-open-loud-and-always-available" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shopping in Turkey is a full sensory experience. Markets are open late, corner shops (&lt;em&gt;bakkal&lt;/em&gt;) are open almost around the clock, and if you run out of something at 11pm, there&amp;rsquo;s almost always somewhere to go.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>